<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Doff" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Doff</orth> (cf. <emph>Daff</emph>) 1) to take off: <cit><quote>d. this habit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 102</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.128" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 3, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 4, 13</bibl> (F<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>daff</emph>). Figuratively: <cit><quote>d. thy name,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 2, 47</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>d. their distresses,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.188" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 188</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to evade: <cit><quote>every day thou --est me with some device,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.176" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 2, 176</bibl></cit> (F<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>dafts</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>